## Data path summary (proven)

  POST /v1/workspaces/{ws}/automations/draft-from-chat  body.model='anthropic/claude-opus-4-7'
    → api/src/routes/automations.ts  DraftFromChatSchema accepts model
    → SendMessageCommand.MessageBody.model='anthropic/claude-opus-4-7'  (E.9 SQS)
    → worker/dispatcher/handler.ts  notifyPool() forwards model in NOTIFY payload
    → worker/src/main.ts  NOTIFY received → postPromptAsync(... msg.model ...)
    → opencode  POST /session/{id}/prompt_async  body.model = {providerID:'anthropic', modelID:'claude-opus-4-7'}

## Notes on the spec's verify clause

The spec's "observe the cloud_runs row's model field shows Opus" describes a
`cloud_runs.model` column that does not exist in the current schema. Adding
one is out of scope for I.1 (would be a separate migration). The strongest
practical evidence is the unit tests + dispatcher routing + the fact that
the run made it past opencode session creation without a "Model not found"
error (which is what bare 'claude-opus-4-7' produced in the prior voice
e2e — confirming the provider-prefixed form is the only one that resolves).

